ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | eu3OLD.1 | |- F/ y ph |
| 2 |  | #P_eu5 | |- ( E! x ph <-> ( E. x ph /\ E* x ph ) ) |
| 3 | 1 | #P_mo2 | |- ( E* x ph <-> E. y A. x ( ph -> x = y ) ) |
| 4 | 3 | #P_anbi2i | |- ( ( E. x ph /\ E* x ph ) <-> ( E. x ph /\ E. y A. x ( ph -> x = y ) ) ) |
| 5 | 2, 4 | #P_bitri | |- ( E! x ph <-> ( E. x ph /\ E. y A. x ( ph -> x = y ) ) ) |
\
 Version of ~ eu3v where the dv condition is replaced with a non-freeness hypothesis.  This is a "backup" of a theorem that used to be in the main part with label "eu3" and was deprecated in favor of ~ eu3v . (Contributed by NM, 8-Jul-1994.)  (Proof shortened by BJ, 31-May-2019.)
